      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The idea that religious freedom is absolute is a dangerous and unrealistic notion in a functioning society. While the state must maintain secular neutrality, this neutrality does not equate to allowing religious groups to dictate public policy or undermine fundamental civil rights. True religious freedom exists within the boundaries of the law, meaning one is free to practice faith privately so long as it does not infringe upon the rights or safety of others.",
      "source": "target",
